step-by-step:

* be root and have internet access
* copy a bee tarball (at least version 1.0_rc17) to /usr/src/bee.tar
* install bee on the host system
* cfdisk
* mke2fs -j
* mkswap && swapon (optional)
* mount target partition to /mnt/lfs
* mkdir /mnt/lfs/tools && ln -svf /mnt/lfs/tools /tools
* cd toolchain
* build the toolchain by running the script build_toolchain.sh
* run the scripts to enter the chroot environment:
cd ../basic_system
downloading.sh
prepare_vkfs.sh
entering_chroot.sh
cd ~/basic_system
files_and_symlinks.sh
exec /tools/bin/bash --login +h
* build the basic system by running the script build_basic_system.sh
* configure shadow and set a password:
pwvonc
grpconv
sed -i 's/yes/no/' /etc/default/useradd
passwd root
logout
reenter_chroot.sh
cd ~/making_bootable
* install bootscripts:
lfs-bootscripts-20111017-0.bee && bee install lfs-bootscripts
* customize /etc/fstab
* build the kernel:
linux-3.1-0.bee && bee install linux
* install a boatloader and thus make the system bootable
